3. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - The paper may have implications for security and cryptography, as it discusses a robustness criterion for determining the optimum size of retransmission blocks. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper may be relevant to systems and control, as it proposes a strategy for achieving a constant throughput. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper may be relevant to multimedia, as isochronous data transmission is important for real-time multimedia applications.
